cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of semantic segmentation in urban scenes using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach to handle synthetic images, which involves treating foreground and background classes differently. This approach involves using detection-based methods to better account for the natural shape of foreground objects. Therefore, the paper may also be relevant to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses experiments to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which may also make it relevant to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
